Western Cape Health MEC Nomafrench Mbombo will assess the Screening and Testing Centre at Paarl Hospital today. Mbombo is expected to accompany health workers at the Mbekweni township for door to door screening. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Dozens of health workers are fanning out across the Western Cape on a mass campaign to screen thousands of people for COVID-19. It’s the second-most impacted province, with almost 500 cases. A second death was recorded there over the weekend.  READ: Western Cape preparing for COVID-19 infection spike In the Cape winelands town of Paarl, many residents appeared unsure about submitting themselves to the screening process. Mobile clinics have been set up and nurses are collecting information from residents and handing out flyers regarding the virus. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.